{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G4 child-consistency — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S6 Docs: private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model)]\n\nRan the 7 cross-child interaction modes for this docs child against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56, S2 70c7, S3 fa49, S4 30b3, S5 b7fa). All 7 modes clean — empty G4 findings list for this pairing.\n\nMode-by-mode:\n- implicit shared state: This child documents knobs/behaviors owned by siblings (REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + portability seam from S1; disk-cap/janitor from S2; verified_at_sha + in-toto Statement + HMAC limits from S4; ref/source defaults from S3/S5). Producer→documenter chain is consistent; no shared-state divergence.\n- conflicting assumptions: This child's \"attested mode fails closed while local mode still runs\" matches S1 AC5 (attested fails closed) and S3 AC2 (local in-place dirty read). \"attested (signs, records verified_at_sha) vs local (never signs)\" matches S4 AC1/AC2 and S5's unsigned-reflection. \"origin/main default\" matches S3/S5. No contradiction.\n- dependency gap: Every doc obligation this child claims has a NAMED producing sibling that explicitly delegates to S6: S1 (\"descriptive credential message ... see S6\"), S4 (\"DOCUMENT its limits ... in S6\", in-toto Statement shape), S5 (prose ref/source semantics → \"Out: prose docs (S6)\"), S2 (disk-cap/janitor behavior). The EFS/NFS flock caveat + AWS placement is cross-ref'd to alto-fruit-punch per the parent's Out-of-scope. No undocumented producer; no missing upstream.\n- scope overlap: S6 is the ONLY docs child; S5 surfaces schema-level \"documented defaults\" (machine-facing outputSchema/text) while S6 owns the human prose (setup-doc credential section, trust-model doc). This is a schema-text vs prose split, not a double-ownership of the same artifact. No overlap.\n- ordering violation: Docs logically follow the behaviors they describe (S1-S5); no contradiction — all siblings carry empty deps uniformly and parent AC8 only requires all-closed + green, so no enforced ordering is violated.\n- consumer impact: This child is a pure consumer/documenter; it imposes no behavior change on siblings. Its xrefs (alto-fruit-punch, REB-289) are to out-of-epic trackers per the parent's Out-of-scope, not to siblings — no broken consumer contract.\n- residual references: HMAC limits, in-toto Statement shape, REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR, disk-cap, EFS/NFS flock caveat, alto-fruit-punch xref all resolve to real producers/trackers. No dangling reference.\n\nNote (not a G4 finding on THIS pairing): the standing seam/dependency-gap flagged on S4 (30b3) concerns WHO routes the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py's hashing path between S3 and S4 — a code seam, unrelated to this docs child. S6 documents the HMAC trust model (delegated from S4 AC5) regardless of how that code seam is resolved; it introduces no new inconsistency.\n\nConclusion: clean docs pairing — every documented obligation maps to a named producing sibling or an out-of-epic tracker per parent scope; no contradiction, scope overlap, ordering gap, or residual reference. Empty G4 findings list."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782520612742764001,"uuid":"3aa935ce-45af-4822-bbba-1a5619224fe0"}